Description:
Modern & Walking Distance To Station
Conveniently located approximately 500 metres away from Ginifer train station this contemporary home under 3 years young offers the perfect way to enter the property market. Showcasing 3 good size bedrooms, 1 upstairs with bathroom and 1 downstairs with bathroom, all bedrooms with built in robe, modern open plan kitchen, meals and living area, powder room and a neatly concreted courtyard at the back ideal for those looking for low maintenance living. Other features include split system air-conditioning, garden shed, lock up garage and more. Currently leased for $1738 pcm, the home is ideal for investment or wait for the tenancy to expire and move in. Located only moments away from Furlong Road, Ginifer train station and Sunshine Hospital. Get in contact today to arrange your own personal private inspection.

Description:
Chic Modern Living With Lifestyle Rewards
Please register your interest to participate in a Brad Teal auction. Registrations allow us to maintain compliance with the latest government directions. All auctions will be held onsite and online. Contact us to find out more.
Make your prize property debut, invest or downsize wisely with this impeccably presented two bedroom residence boasting clever design, quality inclusions and a super convenient location. Nestled in a modern boutique block, the home's ambient light filled spaces, generous proportions and towering ceilings are certain to impress. The large open plan living, dining areas are ideal for relaxing and entertaining, while an easy to manage courtyard is perfect for alfresco dining. Accompanying the living spaces is a smartly appointed kitchen displaying stone counters, stainless steel Bosch appliances and quality two tone cabinetry. Upstairs finds spacious retreat/study area with built-in cupboard. There are two double bedrooms, both present mirror-fronted built-in-robes. They are well-served by a modern bathroom, with stone top, double basin vanity and corner shower, and two separate toilets, one on each level. Features (three) split-system air conditioners, alarm, laundry/under floor storage, automated garage. Enjoys close proximity to parklands, Keilor Road cafés, shopping centres, La Manna, schools, public transport and freeways.

Description:
Easy-Living Full Of Style!
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
With its quality enhancements, abundance of light and impeccable surrounds, this home delivers an outstanding low-maintenance lifestyle opportunity in a popular Airport West neighbourhood with close proximity to all the area's key attractions and amenities. Flawless presentation from start to finish, the home's inviting interior comprises two generous bedrooms (large master) both with built-in robes together with a stylish central bathroom with stone-top vanity and separate WC. Add to this a spacious lounge and open dining area accompanied by a contemporary kitchen complete with soft-close drawers, tiled splashbacks and stainless steel cooking appliances. Ducted heating and evaporative cooling certainly enhance the appeal of this delightful home, along with a full-size laundry, alarm system, video intercom, high ceilings and solid hardwood floors. Step outside to discover a private north-facing courtyard with extensive decked entertaining area, plus a landscaped front garden and the added advantage of a remote-control garage. Walking distance to McNamara Avenue shops and cafes, local parks and sports facilities, it's also close to public transport (buses and trams), popular schools, Westfield Shopping Centre and easy freeway access.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

Description:
Large, Flexible & Easy Family Living
*INSPECTIONS AVAILABLE BY APPOINTMENT*
Superbly located in a coveted street this spacious 4 bedroom 2 bathroom brick home has a wealth of space on a good size family block.
Love it for the space, design and function, this generous home offers a big formal lounge upon entry, good size dining/family area overlooked by a lovely kitchen area with ample cupboard storage and a superb full length enclosed alfresco overlooking the low maintenance rear yard, perfect to entertain family and friends all year round. There are four bedrooms in total, master with ensuite and walk in robe, bright central bathroom and separate toilet. Additional features include split system, double garage with off street parking and water tank.
An easy walk to Albanvale Primary School, bus services and parks. A short drive to Movelle Primary School, Brimbank Shopping Centre, Resurrection Catholic School and Copperfield College.
Land size: 504 Square Metres approx.
COVID-19 UPDATE
We are still conducting business during this time but with the safety & health of others and the team as the highest priority.
We will be conducting private inspections only with stricter guidelines so please contact our office to arrange a viewing.
During our Private Inspections we will ask that only one person is allowed into the property at any time. We ask that no surfaces are touched. We will have the property ready for you to inspect prior to your arrival.
We ask anyone that has recently returned from overseas and if you are unwell to ensure you do not attend any inspections. Contact our office to organise alternative viewing arrangements. This also means if you have been next to anyone that may have been overseas or unwell.
We thank everyone for their co-operation & patience during this time. Stay Safe & Healthy!

Description:
A Family Home With An Exciting Future
Residing on a substantial corner block, of approximately 757m2, is an immediately comfortable three bedroom brick home presenting a multitude of exciting future options (STCA). First time offered in over thirty years, the proudly owned home is set amongst established gardens and comprises spacious living room and rear sunroom leading to undercover outdoor areas, ideal for relaxing and entertaining. Accompanied by an open plan dining area is a spotlessly presented kitchen displaying stainless steel Ariston gas stove, ample bench space, storage cupboards and pantry. Placed off a central hallway, away from the living areas, are three tranquil bedrooms, most have built-in-robes. They share a tidy bathroom, central laundry and separate toilet. Extras include tinted windows, gas heater, split-system air conditioner, ceiling fans, ducted vacuum system, rain water tanks, an array of fruit trees, veggie gardens and double garage with direct home entry. In a well-connected street close to primary and secondary schools, Green Gully Reserve, Keilor Central, buses and freeways.

Description:
Renovated Revelation
Gorgeously modernised, this surprising three bedroom home impresses with a fresh interior, superbly spacious covered entertaining area, substantial garden and plentiful parking. Open by design, the abode's leisure spaces include a living room, which flows to a dining room beside an impressively appointed kitchen showcasing a 90cm stove with five burner gas cooktop, dishwasher and stone countertops. A sliding door accesses the vast covered entertaining area, brilliant for barbecues and other gatherings. To the side is a garden with lush grass and a veggie bed, adjoining an open parking area protected by an electric gate. Further parking is available in the driveway and garage and the home has heating and cooling, plus its own street frontage and no owner's corporation.

Position, Potential and Family Appeal
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Enjoyed and well-maintained by the one family since new, this impeccable single-level home provides a ready-to-enjoy lifestyle opportunity along with exceptional scope for those looking to modernize and personalize in the future. The home's interior comprises three generous bedrooms (large master with WIR and ensuite), central bathroom and separate WC. The spacious front lounge leads through to an open-design living/meals area accompanied by a bright kitchen with ample cupboard space. The home also includes heating and cooling for year-round comfort, security shutters, solid timber floors (under the carpets) and a large family-size laundry. Outside discover a sizeable and established backyard along with a front double garage, with ample off-street parking. Walking distance to Fosters Road buses and popular shopping village, it's also close to Steele Creek trails, local parks and sports facilities, easy access to a range of primary and secondary schools as well as the Calder Freeway.

Description:
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSES 1ST JUNE AT 6PM
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
With its spacious floorplan and versatile indoor/outdoor living spaces, this immaculately-presented corner home presents a lifestyle of instant comfort / convenience with many highlights throughout. Offers 3 bedrooms (large upstairs master with WIR and ensuite),study / home office, sparkling bathroom, spacious lounge, open plan living/dining area adjoining a kitchen to satisfy the chef of the family with butler's pantry stone benches ample cupboard and bench space, roomy laundry Other features include Gas ducted heating, cooling, dishwasher & polished timber floors.
Surrounded by a lovely gardened allotment, complete with paved undercover entertaining area, garage/workshop and extra car accommodation via additional front off-street parking. Walking distance to local schools (including PEGS) and leisure centre, it's also close to public transport, freeway access, Centre way shops and cafes. You will absolutely love it !
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance.
Thank you.

Description:
Fabulous family living and entertaining.
A revelation of surprising size, assured style and entertaining panache, this four bedroom plus study, three bathroom residence is an exceptional new family home in a vibrant locale. Incorporating three outdoor areas, it flaunts a spacious living room and big kitchen/dining. Both rooms lead to their own balcony, and the kitchen is equipped to delight with 90cm appliances including a five burner gas cooktop, fan forced electric oven and rangehood, accompanied by a dishwasher, expansive stone surfaces and great storage. Two bedrooms above boast city glimpses and there are two more large bedrooms below, all with fitted mirrored built-in robes. Fully tiled bathrooms include an ensuite, plus theres a powder room. Wide and easily maintained, the rear garden is relaxing and the whole home is enhanced by a security system and automatic double garage. Shops, cafes, restaurants and trams are just a stroll, schools and sporting facilities nearby and freeway access conveniently close.
Inspection by Appointment or as Advertised.
